info.name: Dark Google Black/Mint-Green 2K19
info.description:
A black google background with mint-green text. Thank You for installing.  Original author a3cAnton. Original code, Google Nightblue 2K15. I do have permission from a3cAnton to post this style.

https://userstyles.org/styles/45830/google-nightblue-2k15-by-a3canton

style.css:
/*Google created by Jayden Smith on March 12th 2018, re-edited February 6, 2019*/
/* i really want this to be global */
:root {
    --bg-color1: hsl(220, 15%, 6%);
    /* Main background color */
    
    --bg-color2: hsl(217, 0%, 0%);
    /* secondary background color */
    
    --hilite-color: hsl(161, 90%, 61%);
    /* Selected & hovered items color */
    
    --hilite-light-color: hsl(220, 99%, 50%);
    /* Selected & hovered items light color (clearer than hilite) */
    
    --text-color: hsl(180, 83%, 42%);
    /* Main text color */
    
    --text-shadow-color: hsl(239,8%,50%);
    
    --hover-text-color: #fff;
    /* Main text hovered items color */
    
    --link-color: hsl(137, 89%, 82%);
    /* Links color */
    
    --link-hover-color: hsl(181, 100%, 50%);
    /* Links hovered color */
    
    --visited-color: hsl(137, 1%, 42%);
    /* Visited links color */
}
